race.comment: SIR WOODPECKER (4) has had only one start in each of his first two preps and gone under as favourite both times, including at $1.24 last time out. Hard to come into given that's the case, but he did look good in a recent jumpout win so we might have to give him one more chance. SECRET GLORY (11) has had sights lowered this prep and not really delivered, but there's obviously talent there given that races she was tested in last prep. Don't treat her too lightly. LANGLO CROSSING (8) faded badly first up at Ballarat when in the market. Willing to put a line through that run as debut last seasom and all of his trials have indicated far more ability. SCOOBARTIE (9) made an encouraging debut. Will have taken valuable race experience and fitness from the run. can build on that display.
